{
  "slug": "hookify",
  "name": "Hookify",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Easily create hooks to prevent unwanted behaviors by analyzing conversation patterns",
  "longDescription": "Hook creation toolkit with 4 commands (/hookify, /configure, /list, /help), a conversation-analyzer agent, a writing-rules skill, and a Python rule engine. Generates hooks for 5 event types: bash commands, file edits, prompt submissions, session stops, and a catch-all. Each hook can warn or block. Includes 4 example rules: console.log warnings, dangerous rm prevention, test requirements, and sensitive file protection.",
